    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Category of marine body of water comprising areas where freshwater streams or rivers merge with the ocean. This mixing of waters with such different salt concentrations creates a very interesting and unique ecosystem. An estuary is usually a funnel-shaped stream mouth or embayment where fresh water mixes with sea water under tidal influences.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
